rooms.Name: The winding streets of Cerulean City
rooms.Description:
Cerulean City is very similar to Fuchsia City.  This place seems to attract
the same sort of wiley Poke'mon.  So, if you missed out on a Sandshrew,
Persian, or Jigglypuff, you can make up for it here.

rooms.Description:
Here in the town Square of Cerulean City is a Poke'mon Center, where Poke'mon
can recover after each battle.  You can also log onto one of the many
computers here to check in with Professor Oak in order to see how you're
doing compared to other trainers, and store your Poke'mon in a special
storage system.

rooms.Name: The base of the coastal mountains
rooms.Description:
The tall, rocky mountains here are breathtaking.  They appear to extend right
up to the heavens.  They are so steep there's no way you're gonna scale them.
Would probably take forever anyway.  A nice, wide tunnel is here cutting
right through the heart of them.

rooms.Name: The tunnel beneath the coastal mountains
rooms.Description:
The tunnel path is wide and tall.  You could easily drive a truck through
here.  Although, it would be a bumpy ride with all these rock element
Poke'mon in here.  And if you're all set with the Rock element monsters, try
on a Golbat for size.

rooms.Name: The tunnel beneath the coastal mountains

rooms.Name: Northern Lavender Town
rooms.Description:
You, being privy to some inside information, have heard there's a Chansey on
the loose in Lavender Town.  Just what ya need to add some frosting to your
reputation as a Master Trainer.  The top of the Lavender tower can be seen
just over the horizon to the south.

rooms.Name: The tiny town of Lavender
rooms.Description:
Sitting here on the east coast, is the tiny town of Lavender.  It's going to
be your only chance to snag a Ditto, Eevee, Tauros, or Pinsir.  There is a
legend that tells of a rogue Scyther that has developed unbelievable power.
The legend says the Scyther is somewhere here in Lavender still today.

rooms.Name: Inside the Lavender tower
rooms.Description:
This tower seemed a lot bigger than one room from the outside. Someone has
left the doors open and the place is alive with pocket monsters. Almost
overlooked, a stairway is here leading to the top of the tower.

rooms.Name: Top of Lavender tower
rooms.Description:
A Scyther must have gotten trapped in here somehow and God only knows how
long he's been here.  He looks about as happy to see you as you are to see
him.  He's been keeping fit by feasting on careless trainers that wander in
from time to time.  Is that a tower bell ringing? Nah, it's Scyther's dinner
bell.

rooms.Name: South of Lavender Town
rooms.Description:
You, being privy to some inside information, have heard there's a Chansey on
the loose in Lavender Town.  Just what ya need to add some frosting to your
reputation as a Master Trainer.  The top of the Lavender tower can be seen
just over the horizon to the north.

rooms.Name: Approaching the east bay park
rooms.Description:
It's very peaceful in this part of the country.  A slight breeze from the
East is spraying light mist from the East bay.  Birds are chirping, the sun
is shining, and the relaxing break is welcome.  You can just see the park
area to the South.

rooms.Name: The east bay park
rooms.Description:
The Park is in excellent condition and is completely free of litter. The
grass is comparable to a golf course green.  Beginning to wonder whether
you'd see a Caterpie or Butterfree today?  Wonder no more.

rooms.Name: The bridge over the east bay
rooms.Description:
The sturdy bridge only slightly sways when the waves come crashing to the
shoreline.  Looking out over the East bay, the ocean seems to extend out
forever.  Facing the front of the park to the West, provides a picturesque
view of Vermilion City.  A slight vibration rumbles through the framework of
the bridge.  Is there a Snorlax around here?

rooms.Name: The bridge over the east bay

rooms.Name: The path along the bay, outside Fuchsia City
rooms.Description:
Walking along the wooded, shoreline path, you can't see any Poke'mon but you
can sure hear some activity among the trees.  It almost seems like laughing.
Could someone be seeing past your masterful front? The next monster you come
across will be your chance to remove any doubts.

rooms.Name: The path along the bay, outside Fuchsia City
rooms.Description:
A casual walk down a lazy lane.  Just what the doctor ordered after thrashing
every mob in that lousy town.  They'll be talking for weeks about the
whoop-ass you handed out in front of a sell out crowd.  Feeling pretty spiffy
about yourself aren't ya?

rooms.Name: Celadon City
rooms.Description:
Celadon City is home to some of the strongest Poke'mon, as well as a few
bent-out-of-shape plants.  Just picture Machamp wringing the necks of four
Weepinbells at once.  Skipping town to avoid Machop, Machoke, Machamp and
Primeape is not an option.  This towns no different from any of the other
towns you've wiped out.  Is it?

rooms.Description:
Having just dealt a legendary obliteration of the whole town, you're eager
for more action.  Stay on the path and it shall lead you to more recipients
of the punishment that is your Mastery. :)

rooms.Name: The city streets of Saffron
rooms.Description:
Here on the streets of Saffron City, walk some of the heavy hitters of the
Poke'mon crew.  A Hitmonlee, Cubone, and definitely a Hitmonchan are prize
trophies to any trainer at any level.  You'll only find them right here in
Saffron City, so assemble your best effort and give it a shot.

rooms.Name: The wooded path to Saffron City
rooms.Description:
There's no end in sight for your reign of terror.  You're on a roll and you
must seize the moment.  Follow this wooded path to the next town and further
your reputation where it counts - on the Battle field.

rooms.Name: Vermilion City
rooms.Description:
Here in Vermilion City, be sure to grab a battle with Aerodactyl, Tangela,
Kangaskhan, and Drogonite.  They are mostly rare Poke'mon and this could be
your only chance for a while.  If you get all tuckered out from battle, go
have a nap on the benches in the park east of town.

rooms.Description:

Kangaskhan, and Drogonite.  They are mostly rare Poke'mon and this could be
your only chance for a while. There's a cruise ship anchored out in the bay.
Maybe after you trash this town you can head over and party on the ship.

rooms.Name: Entrance to the research lab
rooms.Description:
The front of the Lab looks like a disaster area.  The glass in the windows
and doors is all busted up.  It doesnt look very secure with the taped up
plastic in place of all the missing glass.  No ones looking.  Why wait for
them to open? You've got better things to do than standing here forming a one
man line.

rooms.Name: The Lobby at the Cinnabar Lab
rooms.Description:
You've heard many rumors about this place.  Behind the scenes trading, free
advice, and the stories about the scientists here who can clone extinct
Poke'mon just to name a few.  Something pretty bad happened here apparently.
The entire lobby is shredded, and the place is so quiet, you could hear a pin
drop.

rooms.Name: Office Suite B
rooms.Description:
The floor is riddled with debris and the white walls are full of holes.
Almost everything in here is unrecognizable.  In the middle of the room are
the remains of a desk and a few awards and pictures are hanging crookedly on
the wall.  Other than that, who knows what this stuff used to be.

rooms.Name: Office Suite C
rooms.Description:
The floor is riddled with debris and the white walls are full of holes.
Almost everything in here is unrecognizable.  In the middle of the room are
the remains of a desk and a few awards and pictures are hanging crookedly on
the wall.  Other than that, who knows what this stuff used to be.

rooms.Name: Office Suite A
rooms.Description:
The floor is riddled with debris and the white walls are full of holes.
Almost everything in here is unrecognizable.  In the middle of the room are
the remains of a desk and a few awards and pictures are hanging crookedly on
the wall.  Other than that, who knows what this stuff used to be.

rooms.Name: The Lab
rooms.Description:
The lab certainly didn't make out any better than the rest of the place.
Jagged pieces of glass, electronic components, and shreds of plastic and
metal cover the floor. Hopefully, whatever did all this damage isn't still
here.  Guess you'll have to help yourself. You aren't gonna find any here.

rooms.Name: The Lab
rooms.Description:
Against your better judgement, you wander through the lab.  After all, there
could still be something of help here somewhere.  In the corner stands a
freezer.  The walls are lined with empty shelves.

rooms.Name: The bottom of the Bay
rooms.Description:
Visibilty isn't the greatest here at the bottom of the bay.  The swift
currents arent helping much either.  Doesn't seem to be much down here except
for some underwater caverns.  The reports of a loner Kadabra living in those
caverns must surely be untrue.

rooms.Name: Through the underwater Cavern
rooms.Description:
The cavern walls are worn smooth from the fast flowing water.  Going through
here without a safety rope would be a very bad idea.  On the wall of the
cavern there are some markings that look almost like hieroglyphics.

rooms.Name: Through the underwater Cavern
rooms.Description:
Here at the end of the cavern, the surface of the water is glowing slightly.
Cautiously you push through the surface to draw a breath, and check for
monsters.

rooms.Name: A pool in Kadabra's Cave
rooms.Description:
The story of the loner Kadabra is becoming more real by each step.  Littered
on the floor of the dark cave are small objects, bones, and charms.  Someone
has been here recently, that much is certain.  The cave continues on a little
further but it's too difficult to tell exactly what waits in the darkness.

rooms.Name: Back of the Cave
rooms.Description:
Here in the den of the powerful Kadabra, those eyes focused on you can mean
only one thing.  He considers you an intruder in his domain and there's a tax
to be paid. Don't bother running, there's no escape once those eyes are fixed
upon you.

rooms.Name: The Poke' Mart
rooms.Description:
The smell of bean burritos and burnt hot dogs.  This must be Poke' Mart. The
aisles are clean, narrow and neat, and there's way too much light in here.
The floor is freshly mopped, watch your step.

rooms.Name: The Poke' Mart
rooms.Description:
The smell of bean burritos and burnt hot dogs.  This must be Poke' Mart. The
aisles are clean, narrow and neat, and there's way too much light in here.
The floor is freshly mopped, watch your step.

rooms.Name: The Poke'mon Gym
rooms.Description:
The Poke'mon Gym is equipped with all the things a trainer needs.  It's also
the hangout of some famous trainers like Brock and Misty.

rooms.Name: The Poke'mon Gym
rooms.Description:
